  "prompt": "What are some ways to put underline and Bold text in Facebook Chat? As previously we can do this by putting text in between underscore(_) and asterisk(*) for underline and bold text respectively?",
  "response": "Facebook Messenger doesn't natively support text formatting options like underline and bold within the chat itself. However, you can emulate text formatting through some creative techniques:\n\n1. **Bold Text**: \n   - **Using Unicode Characters**: You can use special Unicode characters which represent bold text. You can find these characters from online tools or websites that convert your regular text to bold Unicode equivalents. For example:\n     - **Normal**: Hello, how are you?\n     - **Bold Unicode**: \ud835\udc07\ud835\udc1e\ud835\udc25\ud835\udc25\ud835\udc28, \ud835\udc21\ud835\udc28\ud835\udc30 \ud835\udc1a\ud835\udc2b\ud835\udc1e \ud835\udc32\ud835\udc28\ud835\udc2e?\n\n2. **Underline Text**: \n   - **Using Symbols**: While you can't directly underline text, you can place underscores (_) before and after the text to imply underlining, although it\u2019s not true underlining:\n     - **Normal**: Hello, how are you?\n     - **Implied Underline**: _Hello, how are you?_\n\nAdditionally, you can use other creative techniques for emphasizing text:\n\n1. **Capitalization**: Use all caps for drawing attention:\n   - EXAMPLE: THIS IS IMPORTANT.\n\n2. **Emojis and Symbols**: Use emojis or symbols to highlight or break up text:\n   - Example: \ud83d\udd25\ud83d\udd25\ud83d\udd25 Hello, how are you? \ud83d\udd25\ud83d\udd25\ud83d\udd25\n\n3. **Separators OR Multiple Messages**: \n   - Use punctuation or line breaks to separate key points.\n   - Example: \n     ```\n     Hey! \n     \u2014 \n     How are you?\n     ```\n\nKeep in mind that these methods can enhance the visibility of your text, but they are not substitutes for actual formatting options.",
